# Never serve the SQLite databases (or their WAL sidecars) over HTTP. PHP opens
# these files directly on disk, so denying web access is invisible to the app —
# it only stops anyone from downloading openpantry.db / picklist.db by URL.
#
# This is defense in depth. The stronger fix is to move the databases out of the
# web root entirely with OPENPANTRY_DB_DIR (see paths.php and the README), which
# also needs its own SetEnv line here — but that path is deployment-specific and
# is intentionally NOT committed.
<FilesMatch "\.(db|db-wal|db-shm|sqlite)$">
  Require all denied
</FilesMatch>
